ZH:  我们找了很多人，但他们都不肯帮忙。
EN: We asked many people, but they all refused to help.

ZH: 如果你肯去我会很高兴。
EN: I would be very happy if you agreed to go.

ZH: 他肯定不会放弃的。
EN: He definitely won't give up.

ZH: 她肯定会来参加我的生日派对。
EN: She will definitely come to my birthday party.

ZH: 他很固执，从不肯听从别人的意见。
EN: He is stubborn and never listens to others' opinions.

ZH: 我们应该鼓励孩子们肯努力学习。
EN: We should encourage children to study hard.

ZH: 请您务必肯定自己的能力。
EN: Please be sure of your own abilities.

ZH: 你真的能肯定这个决定是正确的吗？
EN: Are you really sure that this decision is correct?

ZH: 只有当你肯承认错误时，别人才会原谅你。
EN: Only when you are willing to admit your mistakes will others forgive you.

ZH: 他不肯向老板道歉。
EN: He refused to apologize to the boss.

ZH: 你想去游泳吗？他肯去。
EN: Do you want to go swimming? He is willing to go.

ZH: 只有你肯付出努力，才能取得成功。
EN: Only if you are willing to make an effort can you succeed.

ZH: 如果你再不肯说真话，就算我们是好朋友也没有关系。
EN: If you still refuse to tell the truth, it doesn't matter if we are good friends.

ZH: 她的父母肯赞成她的选择吗？
EN: Are her parents willing to support her decision?

ZH: 只要你肯担当起责任，你就可以做自己想做的事。
EN: As long as you are willing to take responsibility, you can do what you want.

ZH: 他们很肯定自己团队会赢得比赛。
EN: They are very confident that their team will win the game.

ZH: 他从不肯接受别人的帮助。
EN: He never accepts help from others.

ZH: 如果你肯努力学习，一切皆有可能。
EN: If you are willing to study hard, anything is possible.

ZH: 我们应该肯定他的努力不会白费。
EN: We should acknowledge that his efforts will not be in vain.

ZH: 虽然困难重重，但是我们不应该放弃努力。
EN: Despite the difficulties, we should not give up our efforts.
